quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And recall that We took from the prophets their pledge, and from you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and from Noah and Abraham and Moses and Jesus, son of Mary, and We took from them a solid pledge,"
  33,8,"that He{1}may ask the truthful{2}about their truthfulness. Yet He has prepared for the deniers a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 1<sup><small>st</small></sup> person to 3<sup><small>rd</small></sup> person.],footnotes:2:[On the Day of Judgment.]
  33,9,"O you who have attained faith, remember Allah’s blessings upon you when troops advanced towards you, and We{1}sent against them a wind and troops that you did not see. And Allah has always been All-Seeing of what <span class="h">you do{2}</span>.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from 3<sup><span class="role-mark"><small>rd</small></span></sup>rd person to 1<sup><span class="role-mark"><small>st</small></span></sup>st person],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Amr read it as: “…of what they do.”</span>]
  33,10,"When they came upon you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>from above you and from beneath you, and when sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>swerved and hearts reached the larynges, and you assume{1}about Allah various assumptions.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense, which serves to create a vivid portrait of past events.
